  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-a6e832b3c82d",
  "content": "corvia-server -- --nocapture`\nExpected: all tests PASS, tools_list now shows 6 tools\n\n**Step 7: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-server/src/mcp.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.2): MCP corvia_context + corvia_ask tools; fix corvia_search routing\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 11: Wire RAG Pipeline into CLI Server Startup\n\nConnect the factory function to the actual server startup so the pipeline is available at runtime.\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-cli/src/main.rs` (or wherever the server is assembled)\n\n**Step 1: Find where AppState is constructed**\n\nLook for where `AppState { store, engine, coordinator }` is built in the CLI crate. Add the RAG pipeline construction there.\n\n**Step 2: Add RAG pipeline construction**\n\nAfter `store` and `engine` are created, add:\n\n```rust\nlet rag = {\n    let graph: Option<Arc<dyn corvia_kernel::traits::GraphStore>> = match &*store {\n        // LiteStore implements GraphStore — extract it\n        _ => None, // TODO: wire up when LiteStore exposes GraphStore via Arc\n    };\n    let generator: Option<Arc<dyn corvia_kernel::traits::GenerationEngine>> = None; // M3.1 will add this\n    Arc::new(corvia_kernel::create_rag_pipeline(\n        store.clone(), engine.clone(), graph, generator, &config,\n    ))\n};\n```\n\nUpdate `AppState` construction to include `rag: Some(rag)`.\n\n**Step 3: Verify the full binary builds**\n\nRun: `cargo build`\nExpected: compiles\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-cli/src/main.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.2): wire RAG pipeline into CLI server startup\"\n```\n\n---\n",
